						<summary>

						<p>On a stone lying in a field in the village.</p>						

						<p>This is dated Śaka 1662, Siddhārthi, Kārttīka, śu • .</p>						

						<p>Damaged. Seems to records the gift of land for daily worship, offerings and burning a perpetual lamp to the temple (name lost) at Takkeḷḷapāḍu by Kānugōhi Śivarāyaniṅgāru.</p>						

						</summary>
